{"id":14881357,"mediaExerciseId":"fe715792-39a3-4af5-97da-83ee5c3f5b84","exerciseName":"11","chapterName":"12","chapterTitle":"Some Lessons From Capital Market History","groupId":612363,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":416,"solutions":[{"id":6221616,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we need to solve for the average real risk free rate and risk premium. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The real rate of return refers to the nominal rate subtracted by the inflation rate. For this particular problem, the risk-free investment is the treasury bills. To get the real risk-free rate, we will take the rate of this treasury bills and subtract the inflation rate from it. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Substituting the values, we will get:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{real risk-free rate}&=3.9\\%-3.1\\%\\\\[15 pt]\n&=0.8\\%\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe real risk-free rate is $0.8\\%$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"The risk premium refers to the difference between the risky investment and a risk-free investment. Since the problem asks for the real value, we will also subtract the inflation rate from the final answer. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"We will first get the average nominal risk premium by subtracting the average value for the risk-free investment from the value of the risky stock.\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{average nominal risk premium}&=12.8\\%-3.9\\%\\\\[15 pt]\n&=8.9\\%\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"Subtracting the inflation rate from the value above, we will get the average real risk premium\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{average real risk premium}&=8.9\\%-3.1\\%\\\\[15 pt]\n&=5.8\\%\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe average real risk premium is $5.8\\%$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"3612193d-f322-4f46-b0de-9ad64376aed1","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":6}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881358,"exerciseName":"12","page":416,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"ba6ae3e3-6039-445b-89e2-8f5c2586c958","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-12-questions-and-problems-12-ba6ae3e3-6039-445b-89e2-8f5c2586c958"},{"id":14881359,"exerciseName":"13","page":416,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"7084a16b-0220-41f3-a1ad-6807fab9465a","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-12-questions-and-problems-13-7084a16b-0220-41f3-a1ad-6807fab9465a"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881356,"exercis